Classification.Comment: This copy number gain of 19p13.3p13.2 involves numerous protein-coding genes. Duplications of 19p13.3 are associated with a constellation of phenotypes (Ishikawa 2013, Martinez Anaya 2020, Nevado 2015, Novikova 2017, Orellana 2015, Ozer 2021, Seidel 2014, Tenorio 2020). Thus, based on current medical literature and gene content, this copy number gain is classified as pathogenic. References: Ishikawa et al., Am J Med Genet A. 2013 Sep;161A(9):2300-4. PMID: 23897601 Martinez Anaya et al., Cytogenet Genome Res. 2020;160(4):177-184. PMID: 32369810 Nevado et al., Eur J Hum Genet. 2015 Dec;23(12):1615-26.
